{{Infobox NRHP | name = Antigo Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = Antigo Opera House.jpg | caption = | location= 1016 5th Ave., [[Antigo, Wisconsin]] | coordinates = {{coord|45|8|27|N|89|9|31|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Wisconsin#USA | built = 1904 | architect = Jeffers, J. H., & Co. | architecture = Classical Revival | added = January 12, 1984 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | refnum = 84003699<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} The '''Antigo Opera House''' is a historic [[opera house]] and [[concert hall]] in [[Antigo, Wisconsin]], United States. The brick building was built in 1904 by architect J.H. Jeffers in the [[Classical Revival architecture|Classical Revival]] style.<ref>{{cite web|title=Antigo Opera House|url=http://preview.wisconsinhistory.org/Content.aspx?dsNav=Ny:True,Ro:0,Nrc:id-4294966367%7cid-5,N:4294963828-4294963814&dsNavOnly=N:4294966362&dsRecordDetails=R:HI22024&dsDimensionSearch=D:Antigo+Opera+House,Dxm:All,Dxp:3&dsCompoundDimensionSearch=D:Antigo+Opera+House,Dxm:All,Dxp:3|work=Architecture and History Inventory|publisher=[[Wisconsin Historical Society]]|accessdate=October 16, 2012}}</ref> The opera house could seat 1100 people. In addition to its use for entertainment, the building served as an [[armory (military)|armory]] during [[World War I]] and is now an apartment building.<ref>{{cite web|title=Self-Guided Walking Tour of Historical Buildings in Antigo, WI |url=http://www.antigochamber.com/resources/walkingtourofhistoricalbuildings1.pdf |publisher=Langlade County Historical Society |accessdate=October 16, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424030212/http://antigochamber.com/resources/walkingtourofhistoricalbuildings1.pdf |archivedate=April 24, 2011 |df= }}</ref> The opera house was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on January 12, 1984.<ref name="nris"/>
